    "The matrix N m is the covariance matrix of the instrumental noise of the input maps, and b m is the beam function.",
    "The matrix Y is defined so that it transforms the multipoles of the E-and B-modes into real-space maps of the Stokes parameters Q and U.",
    "However, this method is computationally demanding, so we continue to use the simpler diagonal filtering approach in our work, as it provides a good approximation for our needs.For the ground-based experiments, we will initially perform map combination using the inverse-variance method:χ ℓm = i ω i,ℓ χ i,ℓm, ω i,ℓ = N -1 i,ℓ i N -1 i,ℓ.",
